  "passageParts": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Here's a common scenario that any number of entrepreneurs face today: you're the CEO of a small business, and though you're making a nice\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, you need to find a way to take it to the next level. What you need to do is\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\ngrowth by establishing a growth team. A growth team is made up of members from different departments within your company, and it harnesses the power of collaboration to focus\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\non finding ways to grow.\n Let's look at a real - world\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 4
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​. Prior to forming a growth team, the software company BitTorrent had 50 employees working in the\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 5
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\ndepartments of engineering, marketing and product development. This brought them good results until 2012, when their growth plateaued. The\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 6
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nwas that too many customers were using the basic, free version of their product. And\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 7
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nimprovements to the premium, paid version, few people were making the upgrade.\n Things changed,\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 8
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, when an innovative project - marketing manager came aboard,\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 9
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\na growth team and sparked the kind of\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 10
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nperspective they needed. By looking at engineering issues from a marketing point of view, it became clear that the\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 11
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nof upgrades wasn't due to a quality issue. Most customers were simply unaware of the premium version and what it offered.\n Armed with this\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 12
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, the marketing and engineering teams joined forces to raise awareness by prominently\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 13
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthe premium version to users of the free version.\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 14
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, upgrades skyrocketed, and revenue increased by 92 percent.\n But in order for your growth team to succeed, it needs to have a strong leader. It needs someone who can\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 15
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthe interdisciplinary team and keep them on course for improvement. This leader will\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 16
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthe target area, set clear goals and establish a time frame for the\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 17
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nof these goals.\n The growth leader is also\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 18
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nfor keeping the team focused on moving forward and steering them clear of distractions.\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 19
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nattractive new ideas can be distracting, the team leader must recognize when these ideas don't\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 20
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthe current goal and need to be put on the back burner."
    }
  ],
